I had heard a lot about this hospital. Recently when I consulted it for my baby's treatment I had a pathetic experience.

1. No proper hygeine maintained in hospital premises. One can get the idea about the same from the way a pile of footware welcomes one at hospital entrance.

2. Doctor is taking least care in patient diagnosis. In my case Dr was busy making online payment while I was discussing symptoms.

3. Doctor does not even bother to tell what is the disease or ailment the baby has. Doctor just writes prescription (in illegible handwriting) and then does not bother to explain anything else. When to come next? What care mother should take at home? For how many days the tabs/medicine to be taken all that is left to patient's wisdom as Dr. does not discuss any of these thing with parents.

Hope they consider this points as early as possible as hundreds of patient visit this place everyday for their baby's treatment and care.

I would like the express my gratitude towards Dr. Gaurav Gadhvi and his team.   From the day, we came here for the first check up till the delivery,  they have been supremely helpful and kind.

Our experience got event better when we came here for the delivery.  Dr gave all the attention and did routine check ups and did not rush for the C Section.

Dr Gadhvi has knowledge  of all the latest technologies and helped us with respect to painless delivery and preserving the stem cell.

Entire team of Akshar hospital is polite and humble.  They listen to your silliest questions and responds properly.

Thank you Dr. Gadhvi and team for bringing smile to the family.
